channel.title: How to disable warning in a 562?
channel.description:
Hi,
On my 562 Server compiler i get warnings/messages like: [code] Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. [/code]
So when I am compiling i get this:
[code]Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. Compiling Main.java... Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. Compiling Packet Handlers... Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 50 Percent Complete... Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 100 Percent Complete... Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
I want to know how i can disable this?
Thanks.
